reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, Durable, Excellent Label Maker
reviews.reviewText: PHOTOS WILL COME SOONFor how cheap this label maker is, it is one of the best organizational tools I currently have. Let me go through the pros and what they could improve on.The Pros⭐Print Quality - It works by physically stamping a letter onto a piece of film. Once you have printed out the words you wanted, you would then cut them off with the integrated cut feature. It takes a little time to get used to, but the print is seen and does not fade over time or while in the sun.⭐Durability - I am a very clumsy guy, and so when I dropped it out of my hands several times, I expected the label maker to stop working. I was incorrect. Despite multiple drops of up to 6-7ft, the label maker was fine and suffered no damage. I would not recommend dropping it, though!⭐Adhesive - The film the label maker provides is of superior quality. It does not feel cheap, and even better, the adhesive actually sticks to many different materials. Out of all the labels made so far on leather, popcorn walls, plastic, etc., they have all stuck and have no indications of falling off. The adhesive is top quality, and I can not praise it more⭐⭐The value of this product - This product comes with a label maker with the film already in it and several other roles of film. Out of my week of constant everyday use, I could barely get through the first roll. This product outclasses every other label maker at similar prices with the value it provides.The ConsFor the price, there are no cons to this product. Everything below is just me being very nitpicky.Build Quality - I called the product incredibly durable, but that does not mean it is perfect. The product is completely plastic and is very weird ergonomically.👍 TLDR:This is one of the most competitive label makers with its price compared to the features it gives to the person. This product is a wonderful organizational tool and will make your life so much more convenient. I highly recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super Intuitive + Great for Beginners
reviews.reviewText: I've never used a label maker before, but have wanted one for years, and finally took a chance on this one! I was acquainted with this company as I have one of their mini printers (which I adore!), so I hoped I would enjoy this product just as much. Well, I definitely do!Right off the bat the product was super easy to use. The instructions are some of the best I've seen, simple enough that you don't get confused with a bunch of extra info, but also clear enough to understand! I also really love the included problem guide, it feels like a really handy table for if I ever run into issues in the future, though I haven't yetI love the range of labels that came with the machine as well. The metallic colors are beautiful, and I love how subtle the transparent labels are as well! I feel like there's something here for every use, and I can't wait to use this to aid with desk organization as well as crafting projects :) definitely a new favorite gadget!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars fun and different
reviews.reviewText: I love the results but the initial struggle with the tape wasn't fun. You may have to troubleshoot when loading a new color tape. I had to feed a tiny bit of tape in from the top to give the tape on the spool a runner to force it up and out with the clicks instead of down and back inside the handle. Now that I know that fix it's working great and I love the results in my reading journal. So stylish and different.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I knew this was a low tech item but I've had it for 2 months, used it about 10 times and now it does not feed the tape correctly. I was diligent in lining up the discs and not being too aggressive with it and now the tape will only advance as far as the cutting mechanism before it gets jammed and curls down on itself. Of course this all happened 3 days after my return deadline. Frustrating. A thermal label printer may be the way to go for a more reliable inexpensive product to label unimportant things at home. Or painter's tape and a sharpie 🤪

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this label maker to replace my old Dymo label maker. It just wore out after 30+ years I guess. This one works even better. The labels are a bit easier to read as the tape is a little thinner and thus it embosses very well. Plus was it works with some if the heavier old Dymo tape I had leftover although I much prefer the new thinner tape that came with my new machine.
